32
33#include <ctype.h>
34#include <stdbool.h>
35#include <stdlib.h>

37#include <isc/assertions.h>

41#include <isccc/result.h>
42#include <isccc/symtab.h>

44
45typedef struct elt {
46 char * key;
47 unsigned int type;
48 isccc_symvalue_t value;
49 ISC_LINK(struct elt) link;
50} elt_t;
51
52typedef ISC_LIST(elt_t) eltlist_t;
53
54#define SYMTAB_MAGIC ISC_MAGIC('S', 'y', 'm', 'T')
55#define VALID_SYMTAB(st) ISC_MAGIC_VALID(st, SYMTAB_MAGIC)
56
57struct isccc_symtab {
58 unsigned int magic;
59 unsigned int size;
60 eltlist_t * table;
61 isccc_symtabundefaction_t undefine_action;
62 void * undefine_arg;
63 bool case_sensitive;
64};
65
66isc_result_t
67isccc_symtab_create(unsigned int size,
68 isccc_symtabundefaction_t undefine_action,
69 void *undefine_arg,
70 bool case_sensitive,
71 isccc_symtab_t **symtabp)
72{
73 isccc_symtab_t *symtab;
74 unsigned int i;
75
76 REQUIRE(symtabp != NULL && *symtabp == NULL);
77 REQUIRE(size > 0); /* Should be prime. */
78
79 symtab = malloc(sizeof(*symtab));
80 if (symtab == NULL)
81 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
82 symtab->table = malloc(size * sizeof(eltlist_t));
83 if (symtab->table == NULL) {
84 free(symtab);
85 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
86 }
87 for (i = 0; i < size; i++)
88 ISC_LIST_INIT(symtab->table[i]);
89 symtab->size = size;
90 symtab->undefine_action = undefine_action;
91 symtab->undefine_arg = undefine_arg;
92 symtab->case_sensitive = case_sensitive;
93 symtab->magic = SYMTAB_MAGIC;
94
95 *symtabp = symtab;
96
97 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
98}
99
100static inline void
101free_elt(isccc_symtab_t *symtab, unsigned int bucket, elt_t *elt) {
102 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(symtab->table[bucket], elt, link);
103 if (symtab->undefine_action != NULL)
104 (symtab->undefine_action)(elt->key, elt->type, elt->value,
105 symtab->undefine_arg);
106 free(elt);
107}
108
109void
110isccc_symtab_destroy(isccc_symtab_t **symtabp) {
111 isccc_symtab_t *symtab;
112 unsigned int i;
113 elt_t *elt, *nelt;
114
115 REQUIRE(symtabp != NULL);
116 symtab = *symtabp;
117 REQUIRE(VALID_SYMTAB(symtab));
118
119 for (i = 0; i < symtab->size; i++) {
120 for (elt = ISC_LIST_HEAD(symtab->table[i]);
121 elt != NULL;
122 elt = nelt) {
123 nelt = ISC_LIST_NEXT(elt, link);
124 free_elt(symtab, i, elt);
125 }
126 }
127 free(symtab->table);
128 symtab->magic = 0;
129 free(symtab);
130
131 *symtabp = NULL;
132}
133
134static inline unsigned int
135hash(const char *key, bool case_sensitive) {
136 const char *s;
137 unsigned int h = 0;
138 unsigned int g;
139 int c;
140
141 /*
142 * P. J. Weinberger's hash function, adapted from p. 436 of
143 * _Compilers: Principles, Techniques, and Tools_, Aho, Sethi
144 * and Ullman, Addison-Wesley, 1986, ISBN 0-201-10088-6.
145 */
146
147 if (case_sensitive) {
148 for (s = key; *s != '\0'; s++) {
149 h = ( h << 4 ) + *s;
150 if ((g = ( h & 0xf0000000 )) != 0) {
151 h = h ^ (g >> 24);
152 h = h ^ g;
153 }
154 }
155 } else {
156 for (s = key; *s != '\0'; s++) {
157 c = *s;
158 c = tolower((unsigned char)c);
159 h = ( h << 4 ) + c;
160 if ((g = ( h & 0xf0000000 )) != 0) {
161 h = h ^ (g >> 24);
162 h = h ^ g;
163 }
164 }
165 }
166
167 return (h);
168}
169
170#define FIND(s, k, t, b, e) \
171 b = hash((k), (s)->case_sensitive) % (s)->size; \
172 if ((s)->case_sensitive) { \
173 for (e = ISC_LIST_HEAD((s)->table[b]); \
174 e != NULL; \
175 e = ISC_LIST_NEXT(e, link)) { \
176 if (((t) == 0 || e->type == (t)) && \
177 strcmp(e->key, (k)) == 0) \
178 break; \
179 } \
180 } else { \
181 for (e = ISC_LIST_HEAD((s)->table[b]); \
182 e != NULL; \
183 e = ISC_LIST_NEXT(e, link)) { \
184 if (((t) == 0 || e->type == (t)) && \
185 strcasecmp(e->key, (k)) == 0) \
186 break; \
187 } \
188 }
189
190isc_result_t
191isccc_symtab_lookup(isccc_symtab_t *symtab, const char *key, unsigned int type,
192 isccc_symvalue_t *value)
193{
194 unsigned int bucket;
195 elt_t *elt;
196
197 REQUIRE(VALID_SYMTAB(symtab));
198 REQUIRE(key != NULL);
199
200 FIND(symtab, key, type, bucket, elt);
201
202 if (elt == NULL)
203 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
204
205 if (value != NULL)
206 *value = elt->value;
207
208 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
209}
210
211isc_result_t
212isccc_symtab_define(isccc_symtab_t *symtab, char *key, unsigned int type,
213 isccc_symvalue_t value, isccc_symexists_t exists_policy)
214{
215 unsigned int bucket;
216 elt_t *elt;
217
218 REQUIRE(VALID_SYMTAB(symtab));
219 REQUIRE(key != NULL);
220 REQUIRE(type != 0);
221
222 FIND(symtab, key, type, bucket, elt);
223
224 if (exists_policy != isccc_symexists_add && elt != NULL) {
225 if (exists_policy == isccc_symexists_reject)
226 return (ISC_R_EXISTS);
227 INSIST(exists_policy == isccc_symexists_replace);
228 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(symtab->table[bucket], elt, link);
229 if (symtab->undefine_action != NULL)
230 (symtab->undefine_action)(elt->key, elt->type,
231 elt->value,
232 symtab->undefine_arg);
233 } else {
234 elt = malloc(sizeof(*elt));
235 if (elt == NULL)
236 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
237 ISC_LINK_INIT(elt, link);
238 }
239
240 elt->key = key;
241 elt->type = type;
242 elt->value = value;
243
244 /*
245 * We prepend so that the most recent definition will be found.
246 */
247 ISC_LIST_PREPEND(symtab->table[bucket], elt, link);
248
249 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
250}
251
252isc_result_t
253isccc_symtab_undefine(isccc_symtab_t *symtab, const char *key, unsigned int type) {
254 unsigned int bucket;
255 elt_t *elt;
256
257 REQUIRE(VALID_SYMTAB(symtab));
258 REQUIRE(key != NULL);
259
260 FIND(symtab, key, type, bucket, elt);
261
262 if (elt == NULL)
263 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
264
265 free_elt(symtab, bucket, elt);
266
267 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
268}
269
270void
271isccc_symtab_foreach(isccc_symtab_t *symtab, isccc_symtabforeachaction_t action,
272 void *arg)
273{
274 unsigned int i;
275 elt_t *elt, *nelt;
276
277 REQUIRE(VALID_SYMTAB(symtab));
278 REQUIRE(action != NULL);
279
280 for (i = 0; i < symtab->size; i++) {
281 for (elt = ISC_LIST_HEAD(symtab->table[i]);
282 elt != NULL;
283 elt = nelt) {
284 nelt = ISC_LIST_NEXT(elt, link);
285 if ((action)(elt->key, elt->type, elt->value, arg))
286 free_elt(symtab, i, elt);
287 }
288 }
